cyclone.name: ZETA
cyclone.current_location: about 305 mi SSE of the western tip of Cuba
cyclone.trajectory: Forecast to move northwest, cross the northern Yucatan late Monday, then accelerate north-northwest across the central Gulf toward the southeast Louisiana coast by late Wednesday
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: southeast Louisiana coast (near Buras/New Orleans area)

port.name: Port of Greater Baton Rouge, LA

weather_observation.impacted_coast: Southeast Louisiana through coastal Mississippi and Alabama
weather_observation.wind: Tropical-storm-force winds (40–50 mph gusts) possible late Wed into Thu with 22–24 % probability.
weather_observation.storm_surge: Minimal direct storm-surge threat at the inland port, but minor Mississippi River level rises possible.
weather_observation.rainfall: 4–8 inches of rain possible Wednesday–Thursday with flash-flood risk.
weather_observation.other_hazards: Possible brief tornadoes in outer rain bands and operational disruptions from prolonged rains and gusty winds.
